name: Villa Leona
address: Banjar Klecung Kelod, Tegalmengkeb, Selemadeg, Tegal Mengkeb, Kec. Selemadeg Tim., Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali, Indonesia
review 1: One of the most majestic villas I've seen in the Tabanan area. It's extremely spacious, with direct access to the black-sand beach. The swimming pool is top-notch! It also has a grandeur entrance, dining area, and a tennis court to put a cherry on top. The road access to this villa might not be the easiest as the streets were narrow and the location was a bit secluded, but it will be all worth the journey.

review 1: An amazing initiative to remain and educate local people and foreigners who are interested in keeping the original Bali nature and green life. The lead of this project is Aniek, and amazing Balinese woman, she has a vision for taking care and keep the Balinese nature and has a few sustainable eco projects in the village of Kelecung.
